Fast-rising and controversial singer Portable has alleged that his life is under threat. He alleged some suspected cult members threatened that he had just seven days to live. He spoke less than 24 hours after a clash with hoodlums during his birthday celebration on Saturday in Sango area of Ogun state. In a video on social media, the singer was seen fighting with hoodlums who allegedly demanded money from him.   Colleagues, fans pray for Kemi Afolabi over ‘incurable’…     Lanre Teriba set for US tour     Seyilaw returns to TV as Family Fame host   Reacting, Portable, in another video on Sunday, narrated how he was introduced into cultism and life threatened because he is famous. Upon joining the outlawed group, Portable said he was promised so many juicy offers, including meeting top musicians in the industry and traveling to Dubai but he did not get any of the promises. He, however, noted that he has reported to the relevant authorities to protect him..